<br>
Mez is a set duration.<br>
Charm is not.<br>
CHA does not cap at 200.<br>
INT does.<br>
<br>
Some opinions:<br>
<br>
How in the world do you actually believe CHA helps lower the resist of a spell? It makes no sense, I've seen nothing in EQ to back this up and with my experience as an enchanter (60th) I can tell you CHA matters naught at all when mezzing. For charms, I still have my doubts on CHA, but better safe then sorry. <br>
<br>
It's how people precieve things, if you think CHA helps and you get resisted a few times, I bet putting on your CHA gear you'll still get resisted a few times, but those times you didn't get resisted, you'll remember it and give credit to your awesome CHA. Mez is a just a set duration spell, CHA doesn't lower its duration or help make it stick better. <br>
<br>
