<br>
Initially the roll for it to stick is based on the standard roll agains MR with the standard Mob lvl vs. player lvl bonuses...<br>
BUT<br>
IF you get a resist there is a second roll that is a direct CHA/# vs. RANDOM250 roll.  If your cha/# is greater then the random then your mezz is unresisted.  Now this happens instantanious so you can't really see a delay or anything.  <br>
(and he thinks that the # is a lvl based variable but he never found it)  He estimated that # is like between 10(lvl1) and 3(lvl60)<br>
<br>
