<br>
Myself, I have an unbuffed charisma of 191 and intelligence of 129 now. I've found this balance works out the best. I have the gear to even it out around 150 on both sides.<br>
<br>
I'm usually the baby running around higher levels, as a result, I swear by my charisma. They don't worry whatsoever about taking the younger enchanter around when my mezzes on yellows and reds stick a lot more often then not.<br>
<br>
What I've found:<br>
* Against greens to whites, I don't worry about casting a charisma buff. My 191 works quite well.  Against greens and blues, I switch items down to incandescent wand or crystal grinder, depending on my mood.<br>
* Yellows and reds: I definitely up my charisma. It hits around 213 with Sympathetic Aura (I don't have Radiant Visage yet... *sniff*). As a result, my mezzes are quite reliable.<br>
* Charming: ALWAYS up my charisma. I don't like to take chances more then I already am with charm, and over 200, I've found that charm is a fair bit more reliable. You still get your bad timed breaks, but you get the full duration a lot more often.<br>
<br>
The other enchanter in my guild of equivelant level is at 39 and is an Int-based enchanter. On the other hand, we do things completely differently, yet we get things done. So... the argument is for both sides. This is just my personal opinion and what has worked for me overall. I keep a set of intelligence gear in the bank for smithing and all, though.<br>
<br>
^_^<br>
<br>
Eelinea Sirene<br>
38 Enchanter<br>
Officer -- The Archangel<br>
Tholluxe Paells <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/uslymie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>slymie</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_magentaspot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#330000>(7/19/01 1:04:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=55.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How Effective is Raising Chr in Mezzing?!?</span><hr size=1> Well...... Here's some more. My last post was when I was at lvl 50. I am now lvl 54 and have spent a lot of that time in Seb, Howling Stones, Kael, Sirens Grotto, and Cobat Scar. nothing that has happened in the last 4 level shas changed my feelings on cha over int. I still ahev cha and int both equalized at a nice 199 each. I have notice that sometimes when my cha buff drops and I lose those valuable free charisma points that there are times that my mezzes don't stick, but then again there are times that I am resisted 3 times in a row by a blue frog that I have tashed. So I still do not have any FIRM believe that Cha helps mez.<br>
The one place I DO know it helps is in charm. High Cha=better chance of a lasting charm. As to ulttravoices comment about charm confusing others around ya, that can be very true. BUT, the benefit of charm should never be underestimated. I have been an avid user of charm since level 12. It is one spell that can alter the course of a battle more than any other. When you reach the level where you have Theft of Thought, you will quickly find yourself the one who has mana while others are LoM or OOM. When you get trained by 7 frogs, yer cleric is oom, then shaman is oom and all 3 tanks are down lower than 10% health. you sitting there with 80% mana, and no idea about useing charm will lead to  all of your deaths. One charmed mob can kill every other one in the room. I know because I did it. Yes the charm broke, yes I got pounded. Thats what Rune V is for and yer stuns. Let me tell you a Seb Golem that is quickened will make short work of many things.<br>
<br>
So my suggestion still stands. Keep them both nice and high. Int to have lots of mana, cha to help with the duration of charms and help with mezzes if it does. If you don't use charm give it a try. Yer sure not gonna be useing any mezzes in Kael, and root is even more fickle than charm. We get an unresistable set 48 second charm at level 60 for a reason. Charm is what chanters can do better than anyone. Necro's can dabble with undead, and bards can fool themselves into thinking they are enchanters, but none com close to the power we can throw when we turn a mobs best friend back onto them. <p><font size="2" face="Verdana,Arial">
